Hi,

Akka Typed will fail when using `orElse` on `Deferred` behavior (by using `Behaviors.setup()`) with the following error:

```
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: deferred [Deferred(Behaviors.scala:43)] should not be passed to interpreter
```

It seems like `Behavior` objects will not be properly started when using `orElse` . The code below will reproduce the problem:

```java
import akka.actor.typed.ActorSystem;
import akka.actor.typed.Behavior;
import akka.actor.typed.javadsl.Behaviors;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        final Behavior<Object> behavior = Behaviors.setup(ctx -> Behaviors.empty())
            .orElse(Behaviors.receiveMessage(msg -> { 
                System.out.println(msg); 
                return Behaviors.same(); 
            }));

        final ActorSystem<Object> system = ActorSystem.create(behavior, "hello");
        system.tell(1);
    }
}
```

Is this expected behavior?
